Package com.google.wave.api.impl

Interface Summary
Operation An Operation is a robot initiated change to a Wavelet, Blip or Document.
 

Class Summary
BlipData BlipData is the serializable data representation of a Blip.
BlipImpl The implementation of a Blip.
ElementSerializer Element serialization/deserialization.
EventData EventData is the object used to serialize event data between the proxy and the robot.
EventDataSerializer JSON Serializer for EventData.
EventImpl The Event implementation that wraps an underlying EventData object and can traverse wavelets and blips if available in the message bundle.
EventMessage EventMessage class used to represent a message sent to the Robot.
EventMessageBundle A container for a bundle of messages to be sent to a robot.
EventMessageBundleSerializer EventMessageBundle serialization/deserialization.
FormViewImpl FormView implementation.
GadgetViewImpl GadgetView implementation.
OperationImpl Implementation class for an Operation.
OperationMessageBundle Represents a bundle of operations to be executed in order when returned to the robot proxy server.
OperationSerializer Operation serializer/deserializer.
RobotMessageBundleImpl RobotMessageBundle implementation.
TextViewImpl TextView implementation.
Tuple<A> An immutable tuple of values that can be accessed using Tuple.get(int) method.
WaveletData The data representation of Wavelet metadata used to serialize and send to the Robot.
WaveletImpl The Wavelet implementation wraps a WaveletData object and is used to traverse blips and other metadata if present in the message bundle.
 

Enum Summary
OperationType The Operation types supported by Robots.
